		<Backstory>The world fractured and the brood poured forth angry and hungry into the sudden light. The call started at Cyndrum, an enchantress that spoke to those that hid in dark places and planted their eggs in living flesh. She spoke words unknown to the children of Hallas, and the queen of spiders stirred at such blasphemy.
		
		Though the swamps, forests and hidden caves of Elemental are full of the queen's servants, many more lay in the depths of the world. Creatures inchoate and tenebrous. There are those that spin webs that trap spirits, those that bear their young when enraged so that the young may join in the battle, and pabulum worms so intent on being eaten that they force themselves into the mouths of larger creatures.
		
		But the most tragic of these are the brood. They are discarded experiments of the titans, the results of rock spider eggs planted in a darkling mother's womb. As the hatched they consumed her intestines and burst from her as they would from the fractured world generations later. Though they bore the upper bodies of darklings they could still hear the call of the spider queen, and they followed that call into the heart of the world.
		
		And now she sends them back, to kill those that would bind her children, and to feed on the rest. Some say they capture female darklings and they drag them back into the darkness, none have ever escaped.</Backstory>
